350 grams Dauphinoise Potatoes
2 unit(s) British Chicken Breasts
150 grams Tenderstem® Broccoli
2 slice(s) Serrano Ham
20 grams Parmigiano Reggiano
1 sachet(s) Truffle Zest
15 grams Toasted Flaked Almonds
37 grams Red Pepper Chilli Jelly

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Remove the outer sleeve and the plastic film from the top of the potato dauphinoise tray. Season with salt and pepper. Pop the container onto one side of a large baking tray.
Lay the chicken onto the other side of the baking tray. Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper.
Roast on the top shelf of your oven, 25-30 mins. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

When there's 10 mins of roasting time left, pop the Tenderstem® broccoli onto a baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.
Roast on the middle shelf, 10-12 mins.
When the chicken has 5 mins left, lay a slice of Serrano ham on top of each breast. Sprinkle the Parmigiano Reggiano over the top.
Return to the oven for the remaining time, 5 mins.

When everything's ready, share the cheesy sSerrano chicken between your plates.
Serve the potato dauphinoise and broccoli alongside.
Sprinkle the truffle zest over the dauphinoise. Scatter the flaked almonds over the broccoli.
Drizzle the red pepper chilli jelly over the chicken to finish.
Enjoy!